MyNDkw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/33632490?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli","html_url":"https://github.com/marpulli","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2018-10-12T15:51:32Z","updated_at":"2018-10-12T15:51:32Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"If the only need for this at the minute is to save benchmarking information, should we have an optional `ModelScorer` class as part of the outer loop that does this instead? I'm imagining:\r\n\r\n```\r\nclass ModelScorer:\r\n    def score_model(self, model)\r\n        stuff here...\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm not convinced about the name yet, I'll keep thinking about that","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/EmuKit/emukit/issues/comments/429372615/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"marpulli","id":33632490,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMzNjMyNDkw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/33632490?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli","html_url":"https://github.com/marpulli","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/marpulli/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/EmuKit/emukit/issues/comments/429778315","html_url":"https://github.com/EmuKit/emukit/issues/25#issuecomment-429778315","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/EmuKit/emukit/issues/25","id":429778315,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQyOTc3ODMxNQ==","user":{"login":"apaleyes","id":2852301,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI4NTIzMDE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2852301?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes","html_url":"https://github.com/apaleyes","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2018-10-15T09:46:33Z","updated_at":"2018-10-15T09:46:33Z","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"No, the idea was to give more flexibility in general. At the moment however benchmarking is the only thing that comes to mind.\r\n\r\nImplementation-wise i was thinking of something like that:\r\n\r\n       self.loop_starting()\r\n       while not stopping_condition.should_stop(self.loop_state):\r\n            self.loop_iteration_started()\r\n\r\n            self.model_updating()\r\n            self.model_updater.update(self.loop_state)\r\n            self.model_updated()\r\n\r\n            self.next_points_computing()\r\n            new_x = self.candidate_point_calculator.compute_next_points(self.loop_state)\r\n            self.next_points_computed()\r\n\r\n            self.objective_executing()\r\n            results = user_function.evaluate(new_x)\r\n            self.objective_executed()\r\n\r\n            self.loop_state_updating()\r\n            self.loop_state.update(results)\r\n            self.loop_state_updated()\r\n\r\n            self.loop_iteration_finished()\r\n\r\n        self.loop_finished()\r\n\r\nAnd when users have a loop object, they would subscribe to these events, maybe with something as simple as `my_loop.loop_state_updated = my_event_handler()`. And these events may have arguments too, say loop state, maybe more.\r\n\r\nHopefully the idea is clear, although of course this is very verbose - we don't really need that many events. Let me know what you think.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/EmuKit/emukit/issues/comments/429778315/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"apaleyes","id":2852301,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI4NTIzMDE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2852301?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes","html_url":"https://github.com/apaleyes","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/apaleyes/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subs